    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "Single-agent validation tests each component in isolation, against clean inputs. But in a pipeline, Agent B never receives clean input. It receives whatever Agent A produced. And if A was wrong, B amplifies that wrong with its own error \u2014 not adds to it.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "scene_class": "B04_IsolationVsPipeline",
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 17.97,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "Each agent treats the prior output as ground truth. It cannot detect that the input it received was already wrong. So the error doesn't accumulate \u2014 it cascades. The mechanism is conditioning, not addition.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "scene_class": "B05_Conditioning",
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.32,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 4.0,
      "narration_text": "Every hop is a multiplication, not a sum.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "STILL",
        "source": "ai",
        "motion": "kenburns",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "headline": "Every hop is a multiplication, not a sum.",
            "eyebrow": "THE MECHANISM",
            "topic": "COMPUTATIONAL SKEPTICISM"
          },
          "rendered": {
            "out": "media/B06.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "image_description": "A close-up of a chain of mechanical links, with rust or damage visibly spreading from one link to the next",
      "chosen_media": null,
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 2.35,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "Agent A gets it wrong with one percent probability. Agent B receives A's output as fact and processes it. Wrong outputs compound. By the time you reach Agent C, the system failure rate is dominated by the cascading dynamic \u2014 not by the individual error rates. The interaction pattern is the failure.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "scene_class": "B07_CascadeTrace",
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 18.99,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8.0,
      "narration_text": "You validated each agent at one percent; the compound system fails at thirty.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "DOCUMENT",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "highlight"
      },
      "scene_class": "B08_QuoteCascade",
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 4.62,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "You can't catch this by testing agents in isolation. What you need: validate the interaction patterns. Which agent outputs flow into which inputs. What monitoring detects runaway error propagation. What handoff conditions gate downstream agents on upstream output quality.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "scene_class": "B09_ValidationMove",
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 17.4,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B09.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B09.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "estimated_duration_s": 7.0,
      "narration_text": "Validate the interaction patterns, not just the individual agents \u2014 which interactions are permitted, what monitoring detects runaway loops.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "DOCUMENT",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "highlight"
      },
      "scene_class": "B10_QuoteInteraction",
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.54,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B10.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B10.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8.0,
      "narration_text": "Individual validation is necessary. It is not sufficient. A pipeline of well-behaved agents can still behave badly. The failure mode has no single-agent analog. It only appears when the agents talk to each other.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "scene_class": "B11_Sufficiency",
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.92,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B11.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B11.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "act": "THE EXAMPLE",
      "estimated_duration_s": 18.0,
      "narration_text": "A customer service pipeline: three agents, each tested. Agent one extracts the order number from the customer's message. Agent two fetches the record. Agent three drafts the reply. In production, agent one misreads order O-seven-eight-two-one as O-seven-two-eight-one \u2014 a one-digit transposition. Agent two fetches the wrong record. Agent three drafts a detailed, personalized reply about someone else's order. The pipeline was confident. Every agent was cleared. The error cascaded.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "scene_class": "B12_ExampleCascade",
      "audio_file": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 31.84,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-error-cascade/clips/B12.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-error-cascade/mp3/beat-B12.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "act": "RECAP",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "Each agent passes. The pipeline fails. Because each agent conditions on the last \u2014 and error doesn't add, it cascades. Validate the interaction, not just the agent.",
